970
01:19:10.245 --> 01:19:11.246
You hang in there.

971
01:19:13.123 --> 01:19:14.624
Yeah, thanks, partner.

972
01:19:18.628 --> 01:19:20.422
(snorting loudly)

973
01:19:20.422 --> 01:19:23.091
-(clears throat)
-What are you doing?

974
01:19:23.091 --> 01:19:26.303
I'm tired of sitting here
waiting to see who gets us killed first--

975
01:19:26.303 --> 01:19:28.388
them or your husband.

976
01:19:28.388 --> 01:19:29.681
What are you going to do?

977
01:19:29.931 --> 01:19:32.684
Hey, babe, I negotiate
million-dollar deals for breakfast.

978
01:19:32.684 --> 01:19:35.228
I think I can handle this Eurotrash.

979
01:19:35.228 --> 01:19:38.356
Hey.<i> Sprechen sie </i>talk, huh?

980
01:19:38.356 --> 01:19:41.276
If you listened to me,
he would be neutralized already.

981
01:19:41.276 --> 01:19:45.155
-I don't want neutral. I want dead.
-(knocking)

982
01:19:45.155 --> 01:19:47.532
-Hope I'm not interrupting.
-What does he want?

983
01:19:47.532 --> 01:19:51.077
It's not what I want.
It's what I can give you.

984
01:19:59.252 --> 01:20:01.087
Look, let's be straight, okay?

985
01:20:02.422 --> 01:20:04.299
It's obvious you're not some
dumb schmuck up here

986
01:20:04.299 --> 01:20:05.675
to snatch a few purses. Am I right?

987
01:20:05.675 --> 01:20:07.469
You're very perceptive.

988
01:20:07.469 --> 01:20:09.429
I watch<i> 60 Minutes.</i>

989
01:20:09.429 --> 01:20:10.555
I say to myself,

990
01:20:10.555 --> 01:20:12.098
"These guys are professional,

991
01:20:12.098 --> 01:20:14.100
they're motivated, they're happening,

992
01:20:14.100 --> 01:20:16.228
i.e. they want something."

993
01:20:16.228 --> 01:20:19.189
Now, personally,
I couldn't care less about your politics.

994
01:20:19.189 --> 01:20:21.316
Maybe you're pissed off
at the camel jockeys.

995
01:20:21.316 --> 01:20:24.319
Maybe it's the Hebes, Northern Ireland.
It's none of my business.

996
01:20:24.319 --> 01:20:26.655
I figure you're here to negotiate.
Am I right?

997
01:20:26.947 --> 01:20:29.658
You're amazing.
You figured this all out already?

998
01:20:29.658 --> 01:20:33.036
(laughs) Hey, business is business.

999
01:20:33.036 --> 01:20:34.704
You use a gun. I use a fountain pen.

1000
01:20:34.955 --> 01:20:37.415
What's the difference?
Let's put it in my terms.

1001
01:20:37.415 --> 01:20:40.085
You're here in a hostile takeover,
you grab us for some greenmail,

1002
01:20:40.085 --> 01:20:43.338
but you didn't expect some poison pill was
gonna be running around in the building.

1003
01:20:43.338 --> 01:20:45.131
Am I right?

1004
01:20:45.131 --> 01:20:47.467
Hans,<i> bubbe,</i>

1005
01:20:47.467 --> 01:20:49.636
I'm your white knight.

1006
01:20:51.638 --> 01:20:54.641
I must have missed<i> 60 Minutes.</i>
What are you saying?

1007
01:20:57.269 --> 01:21:00.272
The guy upstairs who's fucking things up?
Huh?

1008
01:21:04.609 --> 01:21:06.194
I can give him to you.

1009
01:21:10.448 --> 01:21:11.408
<i>McCLANE (on radio): Oh, God!</i>

1010
01:21:13.660 --> 01:21:15.745
Roy! Roy, you all right?

1011
01:21:17.372 --> 01:21:19.708
Just trying to fire down
a thousand-year-old Twinkie.

1012
01:21:19.708 --> 01:21:22.002
(spits)

1013
01:21:22.002 --> 01:21:23.753
What do they put in these things, anyway?

1014
01:21:24.004 --> 01:21:25.755
Sugar-enriched flour,

1015
01:21:26.006 --> 01:21:28.383
partially hydrogenated vegetable oil,

1016
01:21:28.383 --> 01:21:29.634
polysorbate 60

1017
01:21:29.634 --> 01:21:31.678
<i>and yellow dye number five.</i>

1018
01:21:31.678 --> 01:21:34.806
<i>Just everything a growing boy needs.</i>

1019
01:21:34.806 --> 01:21:37.225
How many kids you got, Al?

1020
01:21:37.225 --> 01:21:39.603
<i>Well, as a matter of fact,</i>
<i>my wife is working on our first.</i>

1021
01:21:41.187 --> 01:21:43.231
How about you, cowboy?

1022
01:21:43.231 --> 01:21:45.275
You got any kids back on your ranch?

1023
01:21:46.776 --> 01:21:49.696
Yeah. Two.

1024
01:21:49.696 --> 01:21:54.075
I sure hope I can see 'em swinging
on a jungle gym with Al Jr. someday.

1025
01:21:54.075 --> 01:21:56.119
POWELL: (chuckling)

1026
01:21:56.119 --> 01:21:58.538
<i>Well, now, that's a date.</i>

1027
01:21:58.538 --> 01:22:01.166
<i>But, uh, you're gonna have</i>
<i>to bring the ice cream.</i>

1028
01:22:01.166 --> 01:22:04.169
<i>HANS (on radio):</i>
<i>Touching, cowboy. Touching.</i>

1029
01:22:04.169 --> 01:22:05.378
<i>Or should I call you...</i>

1030
01:22:06.212 --> 01:22:07.631
Mr. McClane?

1031
01:22:09.174 --> 01:22:11.593
Mr. Officer John McClane

1032
01:22:11.593 --> 01:22:15.388
<i>of the New York Police Department.</i>

1033
01:22:15.388 --> 01:22:18.266
-Get on the phone to Harry in New York.
-Got it.

1034
01:22:18.266 --> 01:22:20.602
Better get ahold of somebody at Dispatch.

1035
01:22:21.603 --> 01:22:24.773
Sister Theresa called me
Mr. McClane in third grade.

1036
01:22:25.482 --> 01:22:27.108
My friends call me John.

1037
01:22:27.776 --> 01:22:29.569
You're neither, shithead.

1038
01:22:31.738 --> 01:22:33.448
I have someone who wants to talk to you--

1039
01:22:34.532 --> 01:22:36.242
a very special friend

1040
01:22:36.242 --> 01:22:38.453
<i>who was with you at the party tonight.</i>

1041
01:22:44.584 --> 01:22:46.753
Hey, John Boy.

1042
01:22:48.296 --> 01:22:49.464
Ellis?

1043
01:22:50.090 --> 01:22:51.424
<i>Yeah.</i>

1044
01:22:51.424 --> 01:22:52.634
<i>Now, listen, John.</i>

1045
01:22:52.634 --> 01:22:55.387
<i>They're givin' me a few minutes to try</i>
<i>to talk some sense into you.</i>

1046
01:22:55.387 --> 01:22:58.473
I know you think you're doing your job,
and I can appreciate that,

1047
01:22:58.473 --> 01:23:00.600
<i>but you're just dragging this thing out.</i>

1048
01:23:00.600 --> 01:23:03.478
<i>Now, look, no one gets out of here</i>
<i>until these guys</i>

1049
01:23:03.478 --> 01:23:06.564
can talk to the LA police,
and that just ain't gonna happen

1050
01:23:06.564 --> 01:23:08.566
until you stop messing up the works,
<i>capisce?</i>

1051
01:23:14.406 --> 01:23:15.824
Ellis, what have you told them?

1052
01:23:17.450 --> 01:23:19.285
I told them we were old friends,

1053
01:23:19.285 --> 01:23:21.329
and you were my guest at the party.

1054
01:23:22.789 --> 01:23:24.624
Ellis, you shouldn't be doing this.

1055
01:23:24.624 --> 01:23:27.335
Tell me about it. (chuckles)

1056
01:23:32.841 --> 01:23:34.426
All right, John, listen.

1057
01:23:35.510 --> 01:23:37.887
<i>They want you to tell them</i>
<i>where the detonators are.</i>

1058
01:23:38.138 --> 01:23:39.472
<i>They know people are listening.</i>

1059
01:23:40.765 --> 01:23:42.308
<i>They want the detonators,</i>

1060
01:23:42.308 --> 01:23:43.810
<i>or they're gonna kill me.</i>

1061
01:23:47.522 --> 01:23:48.815
John, didn't you hear me?

1062
01:23:51.693 --> 01:23:53.361
Yeah, I hear you.

1063
01:23:53.361 --> 01:23:55.822
John, I think you could get
with the program a little, huh?

1064
01:23:55.822 --> 01:23:57.907
The police are here now.
It's their problem.

1065
01:23:58.158 --> 01:24:00.827
Now tell these guys where the detonators
are so no one else gets hurt.

1066
01:24:00.827 --> 01:24:03.788
I'm putting my life on the line for you,
pal.

1067
01:24:03.788 --> 01:24:06.458
<i>-Ellis, listen to me very carefully.</i>
-John--

1068
01:24:06.458 --> 01:24:08.668
Shut up, Ellis! Just shut your mouth!

1069
01:24:08.668 --> 01:24:10.670
Put Hans back on the line.

1070
01:24:11.463 --> 01:24:13.631
<i>Hans, this shithead does not know</i>

1071
01:24:13.631 --> 01:24:15.800
<i>what kind of man you are, but I do.</i>
<i>Listen--</i>

1072
01:24:15.800 --> 01:24:18.762
Good. Then you'll give us what we want
and save your friend's life.

1073
01:24:18.762 --> 01:24:21.514
You're not part of this equation.
It's time you realized that.

1074
01:24:21.514 --> 01:24:23.558
Hey, what am I, a method actor, Hans?

1075
01:24:23.558 --> 01:24:27.395
<i>Babe, put away the gun.</i>
<i>This is radio, not television.</i>

1076
01:24:27.395 --> 01:24:29.397
Hans, this asshole is not my friend.

1077
01:24:29.397 --> 01:24:30.815
I just met him tonight. I don't know him.

1078
01:24:30.815 --> 01:24:32.859
Jesus Christ, Ellis,
these people are gonna kill you!

1079
01:24:32.859 --> 01:24:35.695
-Tell them you don't know me!
-ELLIS (chuckles)

1080
01:24:35.695 --> 01:24:38.364
<i>John, how can you say that</i>
<i>after all these years?</i>

1081
01:24:39.282 --> 01:24:40.533
John?

1082
01:24:41.618 --> 01:24:42.619
John?

1083
01:24:50.710 --> 01:24:51.628
(gunshot)

1084
01:24:51.628 --> 01:24:54.297
(screaming, shouting)

1085
01:25:01.805 --> 01:25:04.432
(screaming, shouting continue on radio)

1086
01:25:05.725 --> 01:25:07.435
Do you hear that?

1087
01:25:07.435 --> 01:25:10.605
Talk to me! Where are my detonators?

1088
01:25:10.605 --> 01:25:12.941
Where are they,
or shall I shoot another one?

1089
01:25:12.941 --> 01:25:16.402
<i>Sooner or later, I might get to someone</i>
<i>you do care about.</i>

1090
01:25:17.529 --> 01:25:19.322
Go fuck yourself, Hans.

1091
01:25:21.366 --> 01:25:23.451
Did you hear that?
He just let the guy die, man.

1092
01:25:23.451 --> 01:25:26.412
He just gave him up.
Give me that headset.

1093
01:25:26.412 --> 01:25:28.373
-That's like pulling the trigger yourself.
-Christ, man.

1094
01:25:28.373 --> 01:25:30.792
Can't you see what's happening?
Can't you read between the lines?

1095
01:25:30.792 --> 01:25:32.418
-Is this on the right channel?
-Yes, sir.

1096
01:25:32.418 --> 01:25:34.963
-He did everything he could to save him.
-(sighs)

1097
01:25:34.963 --> 01:25:37.340
If he gave himself up,
they'd both be dead right now.

1098
01:25:37.340 --> 01:25:39.843
No way, man. No way.
They'd be talking to us.

1099
01:25:39.843 --> 01:25:43.555
Listen, you tell this partner of yours
to stay the hell out of this from now on.

1100
01:25:43.555 --> 01:25:45.431
Because if he doesn't, I'm gonna nail him.

1101
01:25:45.431 --> 01:25:47.559
I'm really gonna nail his ass now.
Believe me.

1102
01:25:47.559 --> 01:25:50.687
The man is hurtin'. He is alone, tired,

1103
01:25:50.687 --> 01:25:54.023
and he hasn't seen diddly-squat
from anybody down here.

1104
01:25:54.023 --> 01:25:55.984
Now, you're gonna stand there and tell me

1105
01:25:55.984 --> 01:25:59.904
that he's gonna give a damn about what
you'll do to him if he makes it out alive?

1106
01:25:59.904 --> 01:26:02.782
Why don't you wake up
and smell what you're shoveling?

1107
01:26:02.782 --> 01:26:04.993
You listen to me, Sergeant.

1108
01:26:04.993 --> 01:26:07.954
Anytime you wanna go home,
you consider yourself dismissed.

1109
01:26:08.288 --> 01:26:09.622
No, sir.

1110
01:26:09.622 --> 01:26:11.749
You couldn't drag me away.

1111
01:26:11.749 --> 01:26:14.586
<i>HANS (on radio): Attention, police.</i>

1112
01:26:14.586 --> 01:26:16.796
<i>Attention, police.</i>

1113
01:26:16.796 --> 01:26:18.882
-This is Sergeant Al Powell--
-Give me that.

1114
01:26:20.049 --> 01:26:22.760
This is, uh-- This is, uh,
Deputy Chief Dwayne Robinson.

1115
01:26:22.760 --> 01:26:25.513
-Who is this?
-This is Hans Gruber.

1116
01:26:26.806 --> 01:26:29.684
I assume you realize the futility
of direct action against me.

1117
01:26:29.684 --> 01:26:31.936
We have no wish for further loss of life.

1118
01:26:31.936 --> 01:26:35.064
Well, uh, what is it you do wish for,
Mr. Gruber?

1119
01:26:35.064 --> 01:26:39.819
I have comrades-in-arms around the world
languishing in prison.

1120
01:26:39.819 --> 01:26:42.071
The American State Department
enjoys rattling its saber

1121
01:26:42.363 --> 01:26:45.033
for its own ends.
Now it can rattle it for me.

1122
01:26:46.826 --> 01:26:50.371
The following people
are to be released from their captors.

1123
01:26:51.372 --> 01:26:54.083
In Northern Ireland,
the seven members of the New Provo Front.

1124
01:26:54.083 --> 01:26:58.880
<i>In Canada, the five imprisoned leaders</i>
<i>of Liberté de Québec.</i>

1125
01:26:58.880 --> 01:27:03.051
<i>In Sri Lanka, the nine members</i>
<i>of the Asian Dawn movement.</i>

1126
01:27:03.343 --> 01:27:04.552
What the fuck?

1127
01:27:04.552 --> 01:27:06.512
(mouthing words)

1128
01:27:06.512 --> 01:27:08.681
I read about them in<i> Time </i>magazine.

1129
01:27:09.891 --> 01:27:13.603
When these revolutionary
brothers and sisters are free,

1130
01:27:13.603 --> 01:27:16.856
the hostages in this building
will be taken to the roof,

1131
01:27:16.856 --> 01:27:21.069
and they will accompany us in helicopters
to the Los Angeles International Airport,

1132
01:27:21.069 --> 01:27:23.613
where they will be given
further instructions.

1133
01:27:23.613 --> 01:27:25.740
You have two hours to comply.

1134
01:27:26.741 --> 01:27:29.535
Wait a minute. Mr. Gruber, this is crazy.

1135
01:27:29.535 --> 01:27:31.537
I-I-I don't have the authority.

1136
01:27:31.537 --> 01:27:33.081
I can't authorize--
Two hours is not enough.

1137
01:27:33.081 --> 01:27:34.958
-(transmission cuts out)
-H-Hello?

1138
01:27:34.958 --> 01:27:36.125
Hello?

1139
01:27:37.585 --> 01:27:38.753
Danny, did you get all that?

1140
01:27:38.753 --> 01:27:40.797
Let's go. We gotta make some calls.

1141
01:27:40.797 --> 01:27:43.007
Do you think they'll even try to do it?

1142
01:27:43.007 --> 01:27:44.884
Who cares?

1143
01:27:47.595 --> 01:27:49.722
Theo, are we on schedule?

1144
01:27:49.722 --> 01:27:51.683
One more to go, then it's up to you.

1145
01:27:51.683 --> 01:27:53.518
And you better be right,
because it looks like

1146
01:27:53.518 --> 01:27:55.103
this last one's gonna take a miracle.

1147
01:27:55.103 --> 01:27:58.147
It's Christmas, Theo.
It's the time of miracles.

1148
01:27:58.398 --> 01:28:01.901
So be of good cheer and call me
when you hit the last lock.

1149
01:28:03.403 --> 01:28:06.572
Karl, hunt that little shit down

1150
01:28:06.572 --> 01:28:07.824
and get those detonators.

1151
01:28:08.658 --> 01:28:10.076
Fritz is checking the explosives.

1152
01:28:10.076 --> 01:28:12.787
I'll check the explosives.
You just get the detonators.

1153
01:28:13.913 --> 01:28:15.123
Hey, Powell, you out there?

1154
01:28:16.582 --> 01:28:18.501
I'm here, John. I'm here.

1155
01:28:19.043 --> 01:28:21.921
You gotta believe me.
There was nothing I could do.

1156
01:28:23.589 --> 01:28:26.092
Well, it's gonna be both our asses
if you're wrong.

1157
01:28:26.092 --> 01:28:27.677
I hear you.

1158
01:28:34.142 --> 01:28:35.977
Did you catch that bullshit
Hans was running?

1159
01:28:37.478 --> 01:28:38.980
<i>It doesn't make sense, man.</i>

1160
01:28:40.148 --> 01:28:41.190
Don't ask me, man.

1161
01:28:41.190 --> 01:28:44.027
I'm just a desk jockey who was
on my way home when you rang.

1162
01:28:44.027 --> 01:28:47.447
The way you drove that car,
I figured you for the street, Al.

1163
01:28:47.613 --> 01:28:50.783
<i>POWELL: In my youth. In my youth.</i>

1164
01:28:50.783 --> 01:28:56.789
...and author of<i> Hostage Terrorist,</i>
<i>Terrorist Hostage: A Study in Duality.</i>

1165
01:28:56.789 --> 01:28:59.834
Dr. Hasseldorf, what can we expect
in the next few hours?

1166
01:28:59.834 --> 01:29:03.087
Well, Gail, by this time the hostages
should be going through

1167
01:29:03.087 --> 01:29:05.757
the early stages
of the "Helsinki Syndrome."

1168
01:29:05.757 --> 01:29:09.177
-As in Helsinki, Sweden.
-HASSELDORF: Finland.

1169
01:29:09.177 --> 01:29:13.181
Basically, it's when the hostages
and the terrorists go through

1170
01:29:13.181 --> 01:29:17.852
a sort of psychological transference
and a projection of dependency.

1171
01:29:17.852 --> 01:29:21.022
<i>A strange sort of trust and bond develops.</i>

1172
01:29:21.022 --> 01:29:23.232
<i>We've had situations where the hostages</i>

1173
01:29:23.483 --> 01:29:25.860
<i>have embraced their captors</i>
<i>after their release</i>

1174
01:29:25.860 --> 01:29:28.112
<i>and even corresponded</i>
<i>with them in prison.</i>

1175
01:29:28.112 --> 01:29:30.740
No, no. No, darling. "Asian Dawn."

1176
01:29:30.740 --> 01:29:34.243
Dawn. D-A-W-N.

1177
01:29:34.535 --> 01:29:36.704
-Sir?
-I-- Yeah?

1178
01:29:36.704 --> 01:29:39.207
-The FBI is here.
-Oh. The FBI is here now?

1179
01:29:39.457 --> 01:29:41.501
Yes, sir, right over there.

1180
01:29:41.501 --> 01:29:44.629
-Hold this.
-You want a breath mint?

1181
01:29:47.048 --> 01:29:49.258
Uh, yeah. We got it.

1182
01:29:49.509 --> 01:29:52.095
Hey! How you doing, man?

1183
01:29:52.095 --> 01:29:54.722
I'm Agent Johnson.
This is Special Agent Johnson.

1184
01:29:54.722 --> 01:29:57.850
-Oh. How you doing?
-No relation.

1185
01:29:57.850 --> 01:30:00.895
I'm, uh--

1186
01:30:00.895 --> 01:30:04.690
I'm Dwayne Robinson, LAPD.
I'm in charge here.

1187
01:30:04.690 --> 01:30:06.567
Not anymore.

1188
01:31:00.955 --> 01:31:03.207
Hi, there.

1189
01:31:03.207 --> 01:31:05.001
How you doing?

1190
01:31:08.296 --> 01:31:11.132
Oh!

1191
01:31:11.132 --> 01:31:15.303
Please, God, no. You're one of them,
aren't you? You're one of them.

1192
01:31:16.137 --> 01:31:18.890
Don't-- Don't kill me.
Please, don't. Please!

1193
01:31:18.890 --> 01:31:21.851
-Don't kill me. Don't kill me, please.
-Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1194
01:31:21.851 --> 01:31:25.938
Relax. Relax. I'm not gonna hurt you.
I'm not gonna hurt you!

1195
01:31:28.608 --> 01:31:30.735
Oh, God.

1196
01:31:33.821 --> 01:31:36.949
What the fuck are you doing up here?
What were you looking for?

1197
01:31:36.949 --> 01:31:40.745
I managed to get out of there, and, uh--

1198
01:31:40.745 --> 01:31:42.914
Well, I was just trying
to get up on the roof

1199
01:31:42.914 --> 01:31:46.000
and see if I could signal for help,
you know.

1200
01:31:47.251 --> 01:31:49.754
It's just through here.
Why don't you come and help--

1201
01:31:49.754 --> 01:31:52.798
-Whoa, whoa, whoa. Forget the roof.
-Come on. Come on.

1202
01:31:52.798 --> 01:31:55.092
I said forget the roof.
They got people all over it.

1203
01:31:57.178 --> 01:31:59.388
Come on. You wanna stay alive,
you stay with me.

1204
01:32:03.142 --> 01:32:04.727
Well, the best way we can figure it is

1205
01:32:04.727 --> 01:32:08.022
we've got maybe 30 or 35 hostages
up there,

1206
01:32:08.022 --> 01:32:10.233
probably on the 30th floor,

1207
01:32:10.233 --> 01:32:13.861
and maybe, I don't know,
seven or eight terrorists up there.

1208
01:32:13.861 --> 01:32:16.113
Sounds like an A-7 scenario.

1209
01:32:16.113 --> 01:32:18.157
Thank you. We'll handle it from here.

1210
01:32:18.157 --> 01:32:20.952
When we commandeer your men,
we'll try and let you know.

1211
01:32:21.827 --> 01:32:23.371
Aren't you forgetting something?

1212
01:32:23.371 --> 01:32:24.664
Such as?

1213
01:32:24.664 --> 01:32:26.290
What about John McClane?

1214
01:32:26.290 --> 01:32:29.377
He's the reason why we have
the information we have up until now.

1215
01:32:29.669 --> 01:32:33.214
He's also the reason why you're facing
seven terrorists instead of 12.

1216
01:32:33.214 --> 01:32:35.800
He's inside? Who is he?

1217
01:32:35.800 --> 01:32:38.386
Well, he might be a cop.
I don't know. We're checking on that.

1218
01:32:38.719 --> 01:32:40.054
One of yours?

1219
01:32:40.054 --> 01:32:41.305
No. No way.

1220
01:32:46.936 --> 01:32:47.812
Do you smoke?

1221
01:32:49.230 --> 01:32:50.898
Yeah.

1222
01:32:55.361 --> 01:32:56.737
Thanks.

1223
01:33:01.284 --> 01:33:04.245
You don't work for Nakatomi.

1224
01:33:07.415 --> 01:33:09.458
And if you're not one of them--

1225
01:33:12.878 --> 01:33:14.130
I'm a cop from New York.

1226
01:33:16.007 --> 01:33:17.883
New York?

1227
01:33:17.883 --> 01:33:20.052
Yeah.

1228
01:33:20.052 --> 01:33:24.015
Got invited to the Christmas party
by mistake. Who knew?

1229
01:33:28.477 --> 01:33:29.937
HANS (chuckling)

1230
01:33:31.230 --> 01:33:34.108
Yeah. It's better than being caught
with your pants down, huh?

1231
01:33:44.160 --> 01:33:45.369
I'm John McClane.

1232
01:33:46.912 --> 01:33:48.122
You're, uh--

1233
01:33:49.498 --> 01:33:50.958
Clay.

1234
01:33:53.336 --> 01:33:54.503
Bill Clay.

1235
01:34:00.885 --> 01:34:02.887
You know how to use a handgun, Bill?

1236
01:34:04.138 --> 01:34:06.265
I spent a weekend at a combat ranch.

1237
01:34:06.265 --> 01:34:08.476
You know that game with the guns
that shoot red paint?

1238
01:34:08.768 --> 01:34:11.479
Probably seems kind of stupid to you.

1239
01:34:12.772 --> 01:34:13.898
Well...

1240
01:34:16.942 --> 01:34:18.361
time for the real thing, Bill.

1241
01:34:27.078 --> 01:34:29.455
All you gotta do is pull the trigger.

1242
01:34:29.455 --> 01:34:30.456
Come on.

1243
01:34:39.173 --> 01:34:41.258
(German)

1244
01:34:43.928 --> 01:34:45.596
(cocks gun)

1245
01:34:50.017 --> 01:34:52.144
Put down the gun

1246
01:34:52.144 --> 01:34:54.230
and give me my detonators.

1247
01:34:58.818 --> 01:35:00.319
Well, well, well.

1248
01:35:02.154 --> 01:35:03.155
Hans.

1249
01:35:04.323 --> 01:35:06.575
Put it down now.

1250
01:35:10.454 --> 01:35:12.415
That's pretty tricky with that accent.

1251
01:35:14.250 --> 01:35:16.335
You oughta be on fucking TV
with that accent.

1252
01:35:19.338 --> 01:35:21.924
But what do you want with the detonators,
Hans?

1253
01:35:23.175 --> 01:35:25.386
I already used all the explosives.

1254
01:35:28.180 --> 01:35:29.390
Or did I?

1255
01:35:31.142 --> 01:35:33.227
-I'm going to count to three.
-Yeah.

1256
01:35:33.227 --> 01:35:35.938
-Like you did with Takagi?
-(clicks)

1257
01:35:35.938 --> 01:35:38.607
-Oops.
-(clicking)

1258
01:35:38.899 --> 01:35:40.609
No bullets.

1259
01:35:40.609 --> 01:35:42.278
You think I'm fucking stupid, Hans?

1260
01:35:42.278 --> 01:35:43.362
(dings)

1261
01:35:43.362 --> 01:35:44.405
You were saying?

1262
01:35:45.865 --> 01:35:48.075
(yelling)

1263
01:36:09.346 --> 01:36:10.931
(shouts in German)

1264
01:36:39.585 --> 01:36:40.461
Karl.

1265
01:36:40.461 --> 01:36:43.589
-(German)
-(gunfire continues)

1266
01:36:49.553 --> 01:36:51.305
Shoot the glass.

1267
01:37:24.630 --> 01:37:26.215
Jesus Christ!

1268
01:37:55.494 --> 01:37:58.330
Smile, Karl. We're back in business.

1269
01:38:01.083 --> 01:38:04.461
<i>...is the last resort of diplomacy.</i>

1270
01:38:04.461 --> 01:38:07.381
<i>Then couldn't we just as well say</i>

1271
01:38:07.381 --> 01:38:10.217
<i>that terrorism has an equal claim</i>
<i>on being that too?</i>

1272
01:38:11.302 --> 01:38:13.178
You got something.
Tell me you got something.

1273
01:38:13.178 --> 01:38:15.806
Just McClane's name, badge number,
employment record,

1274
01:38:16.056 --> 01:38:18.642
vital statistics
and his family's home address...

1275
01:38:19.476 --> 01:38:20.728
right here in L.A.

1276
01:38:22.813 --> 01:38:23.731
Whoa!

1277
01:38:24.690 --> 01:38:26.066
(elevator bell dings)

1278
01:38:28.736 --> 01:38:30.654
HANS: Go to work.

1279
01:38:30.654 --> 01:38:32.031
Got it.

1280
01:38:44.668 --> 01:38:48.422
God, that man looks really pissed.

1281
01:38:50.174 --> 01:38:52.593
He's still alive.

1282
01:38:52.593 --> 01:38:53.844
What?

1283
01:38:55.220 --> 01:38:58.265
Only John can drive somebody that crazy.

1284
01:39:00.267 --> 01:39:02.436
(panting)

1285
01:39:02.436 --> 01:39:03.771
(grunts)

1286
01:39:13.781 --> 01:39:16.575
-(beeping)
-THEO: Hans.

1287
01:39:16.575 --> 01:39:19.244
You better heat up that miracle, because
we just broke through on number six,

1288
01:39:19.244 --> 01:39:21.789
and the electromagnetic
came down like a fucking anvil.

1289
01:39:22.081 --> 01:39:26.543
Have a look at what our friends outside
are doing, and I'll be right up.

1290
01:39:27.378 --> 01:39:29.171
(water running)

1291
01:39:29.713 --> 01:39:31.465
<i>POWELL: Hey, John?</i>

1292
01:39:31.465 --> 01:39:33.509
<i>John McClane, you still with us?</i>

1293
01:39:33.509 --> 01:39:34.635
Yeah.

1294
01:39:35.636 --> 01:39:38.597
But all things being equal,
I'd rather be in Philadelphia.

1295
01:39:39.807 --> 01:39:41.892
Chalk up two more bad guys.

1296
01:39:42.810 --> 01:39:46.230
<i>Well, the boys down here</i>
<i>will be glad to hear that.</i>

1297
01:39:46.230 --> 01:39:48.524
<i>You know, we got a pool going on you.</i>

1298
01:39:48.524 --> 01:39:50.317
What kind of odds am I gettin'?

1299
01:39:50.317 --> 01:39:51.735
<i>You don't want to know.</i>

1300
01:39:51.735 --> 01:39:54.530
Put me down for 20. I'm good for it.

1301
01:39:58.242 --> 01:40:01.286
<i>McCLANE: Hey, Powell, you got flat feet?</i>

1302
01:40:03.539 --> 01:40:05.624
What the hell you talking about, man?

1303
01:40:05.624 --> 01:40:08.252
Something had to get you off the street.

1304
01:40:08.711 --> 01:40:11.213
<i>What's the matter? You don't think</i>
<i>jockeying papers across a desk</i>

1305
01:40:11.213 --> 01:40:13.590
<i>is a noble effort for a cop?</i>

1306
01:40:15.134 --> 01:40:16.885
<i>McCLANE: No.</i>

1307
01:40:19.722 --> 01:40:21.306
I had an accident.

1308
01:40:21.306 --> 01:40:23.642
<i>The way you drive, I can see why.</i>

1309
01:40:23.642 --> 01:40:27.354
What'd you do, run over your
captain's foot with a car?

1310
01:40:30.816 --> 01:40:32.401
I shot a kid.

1311
01:40:33.902 --> 01:40:35.779
<i>He was 13-years-old.</i>

1312
01:40:37.698 --> 01:40:39.616
<i>It was dark. I couldn't see him.</i>

1313
01:40:39.616 --> 01:40:41.201
<i>He had a ray gun. It looked real enough.</i>

1314
01:40:44.371 --> 01:40:47.666
You know, when you're a rookie, they can
teach you everything about being a cop,

1315
01:40:47.666 --> 01:40:49.918
except how to live with a mistake.

1316
01:40:54.423 --> 01:40:57.926
<i>Anyway, I just couldn't bring myself</i>
<i>to draw my gun on anybody again.</i>

1317
01:41:01.889 --> 01:41:03.557
<i>McCLANE: Sorry, man.</i>

1318
01:41:04.683 --> 01:41:07.436
Hey, man, how could you know?

1319
01:41:09.730 --> 01:41:11.523
I feel like shit anyway.

1320
01:41:14.818 --> 01:41:16.361
Well, then this won't matter.

1321
01:41:17.488 --> 01:41:20.908
The LAPD is not calling
the shots down here anymore.

1322
01:41:23.452 --> 01:41:24.703
Feds?

1323
01:41:24.703 --> 01:41:26.205
You got it.

1324
01:41:27.706 --> 01:41:30.584
All right, those are the city engineers.

1325
01:41:32.711 --> 01:41:34.880
They're going into the street circuits.

1326
01:41:35.923 --> 01:41:37.925
Those guys in the suits--
I don't know who they are.

1327
01:41:37.925 --> 01:41:38.967
HANS: That's the FBI.

1328
01:41:40.427 --> 01:41:43.514
They're ordering the others
to cut the building's power.

1329
01:41:43.514 --> 01:41:45.599
Regular as clockwork.

1330
01:41:47.267 --> 01:41:49.561
Or a time lock.

1331
01:41:49.561 --> 01:41:51.438
HANS: Precisely.

1332
01:41:51.438 --> 01:41:53.941
The circuits that cannot be cut

1333
01:41:53.941 --> 01:41:55.734
are cut automatically

1334
01:41:55.734 --> 01:41:58.320
in response to a terrorist incident.

1335
01:41:58.320 --> 01:42:00.948
You asked for miracles, Theo.
I give you

1336
01:42:00.948 --> 01:42:03.951
the FBI.

1337
01:42:04.576 --> 01:42:06.537
I said I want the friggin' building
shut down.

1338
01:42:06.537 --> 01:42:08.831
I got a problem. I got a switch here--

1339
01:42:08.831 --> 01:42:10.958
I don't give two shits about your switch!

1340
01:42:11.250 --> 01:42:14.002
-I want the building out. Dark. D-A-R-K!
-Hold on! You don't understand.

1341
01:42:14.002 --> 01:42:16.004
-You can't do it from here.
-Yeah, you could.

1342
01:42:16.213 --> 01:42:17.881
It can't be done from here.

1343
01:42:17.881 --> 01:42:19.007
I could just-- I got the radio.

1344
01:42:19.299 --> 01:42:23.428
We can't do it from down here, I'm telling
you. It's gotta be done from downtown.

1345
01:42:23.428 --> 01:42:25.514
They've gotta take out
a whole city grid.

1346
01:42:25.514 --> 01:42:27.766
-We're talking ten square blocks.
-Ten blocks?

1347
01:42:27.766 --> 01:42:29.852
Johnson, that's crazy.
It's Christmas Eve, man.

1348
01:42:29.852 --> 01:42:33.564
-There's thousands of people--
-JOHNSON: You have to go wider.

1349
01:42:33.564 --> 01:42:35.649
-I need authorization.
-Authorization?

1350
01:42:35.649 --> 01:42:37.693
How about the United States
fucking government?

1351
01:42:37.693 --> 01:42:38.652
Hey.

1352
01:42:38.652 --> 01:42:40.737
Lose the grid or you lose your job.

1353
01:42:47.035 --> 01:42:48.704
-Yeah, Central?
<i>-MAN: Yeah?</i>

1354
01:42:48.704 --> 01:42:52.624
This is Walt down at Nakatomi.
Say, listen.

1355
01:42:52.624 --> 01:42:56.628
Would it be possible
for you to turn off grid 212?

1356
01:42:56.628 --> 01:43:00.048
<i>-Are you crazy?</i>
-Maybe I should call the mayor.

1357
01:43:00.299 --> 01:43:03.051
No shit, it's my ass. I got
a big problem down here. Shut it down.

1358
01:43:03.343 --> 01:43:05.012
Shut it down now.

1359
01:43:09.516 --> 01:43:12.060
<i>FEMALE COMPUTERIZED VOICE:</i>
<i>Emergency lighting activated.</i>

1360
01:43:12.060 --> 01:43:14.980
Powell. Powell, talk to me.
What's going on here?

1361
01:43:14.980 --> 01:43:16.523
<i>POWELL: Ask the FBI.</i>

1362
01:43:16.523 --> 01:43:19.067
They got the universal terrorist playbook,

1363
01:43:19.318 --> 01:43:21.695
and they're running it step by step.

1364
01:43:23.697 --> 01:43:25.782
THEO: It's gonna go. It's gonna go!

1365
01:43:25.782 --> 01:43:28.952
-(latches unlocking)
-Yes!

1366
01:43:28.952 --> 01:43:30.662
(alarm blaring)

1367
01:43:45.344 --> 01:43:47.012
(alarm stops)

1368
01:43:51.600 --> 01:43:53.602
Merry Christmas.

1369
01:43:55.854 --> 01:43:57.856
Those bastards are probably
pissing in their pants right now.

1370
01:43:57.856 --> 01:43:59.733
The mayor's gonna have my ass.

1371
01:44:06.990 --> 01:44:08.867
Whoo!

1372
01:44:21.129 --> 01:44:24.633
Well, what are we gonna do now?

1373
01:44:24.633 --> 01:44:27.177
Arrest them for not paying
their electric bill?

1374
01:44:27.177 --> 01:44:28.679
We've shut them down.

1375
01:44:28.679 --> 01:44:32.015
We let 'em sweat for a while,
then we give 'em helicopters.

1376
01:44:32.015 --> 01:44:34.184
Right up the ass.

1377
01:44:37.020 --> 01:44:38.939
This is Agent Johnson.

1378
01:44:38.939 --> 01:44:40.524
No, the other one.

1379
01:44:40.524 --> 01:44:43.568
I want that air support ready to lift off
in five minutes.

1380
01:44:43.568 --> 01:44:46.571
Damn right. Fully armed. We're on the way.

1381
01:44:50.951 --> 01:44:54.413
(snickering quietly) Oh, yeah!

1382
01:44:56.581 --> 01:44:58.709
I wish to talk to the FBI.

1383
01:45:01.503 --> 01:45:03.588
This is Special Agent Johnson of the FBI.

1384
01:45:03.588 --> 01:45:08.051
<i>The State Department has arranged</i>
<i>for the return of your comrades.</i>

1385
01:45:08.051 --> 01:45:10.804
Helicopters are en route as you requested.

1386
01:45:10.804 --> 01:45:13.515
<i>I hear you. We'll be ready.</i>

1387
01:45:13.515 --> 01:45:15.684
By the time he figures out what hit him,
he'll be in a body bag.

1388
01:45:15.684 --> 01:45:18.061
When they touch down,
we'll blow the roof.

1389
01:45:18.061 --> 01:45:19.813
They'll spend a month
sifting through the rubble.

1390
01:45:19.813 --> 01:45:22.190
And by the time they figure out
what went wrong,

1391
01:45:22.190 --> 01:45:25.652
we'll be sitting on a beach
earning 20 percent.

1392
01:45:30.490 --> 01:45:32.075
(groans)

1393
01:45:32.075 --> 01:45:34.077
Powell.

1394
01:45:34.077 --> 01:45:35.746
Yo, Powell, you got a minute?

1395
01:45:37.497 --> 01:45:39.124
I'm here, John.

1396
01:45:41.126 --> 01:45:44.129
Listen, man, I'm starting
to get a bad feeling up here.

1397
01:45:44.755 --> 01:45:46.715
I want you to do something for me.

1398
01:45:46.715 --> 01:45:47.799
Um--

1399
01:45:49.718 --> 01:45:53.847
I want you to find my wife. Don't ask me
how. By then, you'll know how.

1400
01:45:53.847 --> 01:45:56.975
Uh, I want you to tell her something.

1401
01:45:58.185 --> 01:45:59.936
I want you to tell her that...

1402
01:46:00.771 --> 01:46:01.813
um...

1403
01:46:07.110 --> 01:46:09.654
Tell her it took me a while
to figure out...

1404
01:46:10.197 --> 01:46:13.533
what a jerk I've been, but, um...

1405
01:46:15.160 --> 01:46:16.661
but that...

1406
01:46:20.540 --> 01:46:23.835
that when things started to
pan out for her, I should've...

1407
01:46:25.796 --> 01:46:27.589
been more supportive,

1408
01:46:27.589 --> 01:46:28.256
and, uh...

1409
01:46:30.008 --> 01:46:32.219
<i>and I just should've been behind her more.</i>

1410
01:46:32.219 --> 01:46:34.596
(panting)

1411
01:46:34.596 --> 01:46:36.765
Oh, shit.

1412
01:46:39.810 --> 01:46:41.603
Tell her that, um--

1413
01:46:43.146 --> 01:46:46.233
that she's the best thing
that ever happened to a bum like me.

1414
01:46:49.236 --> 01:46:52.030
She's heard me say "I love you"
a thousand times.

1415
01:46:54.074 --> 01:46:56.201
She never heard me say, "I'm sorry."

1416
01:46:58.036 --> 01:47:00.747
And I want you to tell her that.
I want you to tell her that...

1417
01:47:01.998 --> 01:47:04.543
"John said that he was sorry."

1418
01:47:05.544 --> 01:47:06.545
Okay?

1419
01:47:07.712 --> 01:47:09.131
You got that, man?

1420
01:47:09.756 --> 01:47:10.882
<i>Yeah, I got it, John.</i>

1421
01:47:12.175 --> 01:47:15.011
But you can tell her that yourself.

1422
01:47:15.011 --> 01:47:17.764
You just watch your ass, and you'll
make it out of there. You hear me?

1423
01:47:19.307 --> 01:47:21.685
<i>Well, I guess that's up to</i>
<i>the man upstairs.</i>

1424
01:47:25.564 --> 01:47:27.274
<i>John?</i>

1425
01:47:27.274 --> 01:47:29.276
<i>John?</i>

1426
01:47:29.276 --> 01:47:31.570
What the fuck were you doing upstairs,
Hans?

1427
01:47:34.322 --> 01:47:37.117
<i>-John?</i>
-No, Al, listen.

1428
01:47:37.117 --> 01:47:38.743
Listen, just lay off for a while.

1429
01:47:40.829 --> 01:47:42.914
<i>I gotta go check on something.</i>

1430
01:47:46.042 --> 01:47:48.670
-One minute. That's all I'm asking.
-(Spanish)

1431
01:47:48.670 --> 01:47:51.673
One minute just to speak to you.
All right. All right.

1432
01:47:51.673 --> 01:47:54.885
All right. Get back.
Get back. Off. Off. All right.

1433
01:47:54.885 --> 01:47:58.346
Look, you let me in right now,
or I call the INS.

1434
01:47:58.346 --> 01:47:59.973
<i>Comprende?</i>

1435
01:48:01.391 --> 01:48:03.101
Look, this is the last time

1436
01:48:03.101 --> 01:48:05.687
these kids are gonna have
to speak to their parents.

1437
01:48:08.273 --> 01:48:11.902
All right? All right.
Come on. Come on.

1438
01:48:22.913 --> 01:48:26.166
What were you doing, Hans?
What were you doing?

1439
01:48:41.014 --> 01:48:44.309
(beeping)

1440
01:48:47.938 --> 01:48:50.690
Jesus, Mary, mother of God.

1441
01:48:54.903 --> 01:48:57.113
Powell, Powell, listen to me!
It's a double cross!

1442
01:48:57.113 --> 01:48:58.990
The whole roof
of the building's wired to--

1443
01:49:01.993 --> 01:49:03.954
<i>POWELL: John.</i>

1444
01:49:05.872 --> 01:49:07.165
<i>John.</i>

1445
01:49:07.165 --> 01:49:10.085
John, come in. Did you get that?

1446
01:49:10.085 --> 01:49:12.295
No. Something about a double cross.

1447
01:49:13.672 --> 01:49:15.048
Tell me about it.

1448
01:49:21.304 --> 01:49:23.390
We are both professionals.

1449
01:49:25.809 --> 01:49:27.269
This is personal.

1450
01:49:28.728 --> 01:49:29.813
Oh.

1451
01:49:50.959 --> 01:49:52.294
They're coming.

1452
01:49:53.962 --> 01:49:56.131
-Choppers are coming.
-Okay.

1453
01:49:56.131 --> 01:49:59.217
Time to gather your flock, Miss Gennero.

1454
01:50:00.093 --> 01:50:02.304
<i>THORNBURG: Your mom and dad</i>
<i>are very important people.</i>

1455
01:50:02.304 --> 01:50:05.932
<i>They're very brave people.</i>

1456
01:50:05.932 --> 01:50:08.893
<i>So is there something you would like</i>
<i>to say to them if they're watching?</i>

1457
01:50:10.312 --> 01:50:12.105
<i>Come home.</i>

1458
01:50:21.281 --> 01:50:22.449
Mrs. McClane.

1459
01:50:26.202 --> 01:50:28.747
How nice to make your acquaintance.

1460
01:50:29.914 --> 01:50:32.792
(screaming, shouting)

1461
01:50:32.792 --> 01:50:34.377
On your feet, everyone! To the roof!

1462
01:50:34.377 --> 01:50:36.921
Lock them up there and come right back.

1463
01:50:39.382 --> 01:50:41.426
MAN: Move! Come on! Let's move!

1464
01:51:06.159 --> 01:51:08.328
You should've heard your brother squeal

1465
01:51:08.328 --> 01:51:10.288
when I broke his fucking neck!

1466
01:51:13.541 --> 01:51:16.252
What do you figure the breakage?

1467
01:51:16.252 --> 01:51:18.338
Figure we take out the terrorists,

1468
01:51:18.338 --> 01:51:22.092
lose 20--25 percent of the hostages...
tops.

1469
01:51:22.092 --> 01:51:24.594
I can live with that.

1470
01:51:24.886 --> 01:51:26.137
Keep this thing on the deck.

1471
01:51:26.137 --> 01:51:29.474
They're expecting transports,
not gunships.

1472
01:51:41.361 --> 01:51:44.155
Move it! Come on! Move!

1473
01:51:44.155 --> 01:51:45.156
Come on! Come on!

1474
01:51:45.156 --> 01:51:46.491
Move it!

1475
01:51:47.534 --> 01:51:49.327
Let's go! Move!

1476
01:51:53.039 --> 01:51:56.000
Theo. A little bonus for us.

1477
01:51:56.000 --> 01:51:58.920
-Please, sit down. Sit down.
-Hey!

1478
01:51:58.920 --> 01:52:01.005
A policeman's wife might come in handy.

1479
01:52:01.005 --> 01:52:03.216
McClane, I have some news for you.

1480
01:52:04.509 --> 01:52:05.969
McClane.

1481
01:52:13.476 --> 01:52:15.353
(groans)

1482
01:52:17.147 --> 01:52:18.982
Come on! Move, move!

1483
01:52:21.109 --> 01:52:23.069
Come on!

1484
01:52:34.831 --> 01:52:36.916
Motherfucker, I'll kill you!

1485
01:52:40.170 --> 01:52:43.298
-(beeping)
-Armed. The truck?

1486
01:52:43.298 --> 01:52:44.424
The truck.

1487
01:52:52.056 --> 01:52:53.933
After all your posturing,

1488
01:52:53.933 --> 01:52:55.602
all your little speeches,

1489
01:52:55.602 --> 01:52:57.520
you're nothing but a common thief.

1490
01:52:59.105 --> 01:53:01.232
I am an exceptional thief, Mrs. McClane.

1491
01:53:01.232 --> 01:53:04.152
And since I'm moving up to kidnapping,
you should be more polite.

1492
01:53:11.618 --> 01:53:13.953
Motherfucker, I'm gonna kill you!

1493
01:53:13.953 --> 01:53:15.663
I'm gonna fucking cook you,

1494
01:53:15.663 --> 01:53:17.290
and I'm gonna fucking eat you!

1495
01:53:40.021 --> 01:53:42.065
I don't like this, Sarge.

1496
01:53:50.156 --> 01:53:52.659
(whooping)

1497
01:53:52.659 --> 01:53:55.954
Just like fuckin' Saigon, eh, slick?

1498
01:53:57.539 --> 01:54:00.124
I was in junior high, dickhead.

1499
01:54:17.100 --> 01:54:19.143
(panicked chattering)

1500
01:54:28.528 --> 01:54:31.489
Where's Holly? Where's Holly Gennero?

1501
01:54:31.489 --> 01:54:33.408
Holly Gennero! Where's Holly?

1502
01:54:33.408 --> 01:54:35.243
Where's Holly? Where is she?

1503
01:54:35.243 --> 01:54:36.744
-They took her!
-Where?

1504
01:54:36.744 --> 01:54:38.746
-The vault!
-Where is the vault?

1505
01:54:38.746 --> 01:54:41.291
The 30th floor. Up the stairs.
They just took her!

1506
01:54:43.376 --> 01:54:44.711
Get downstairs, all of you!

1507
01:54:44.711 --> 01:54:47.589
The whole fuckin' roof is wired to blow.
Get down!

1508
01:54:47.589 --> 01:54:50.341
Get down! Get the fuck downstairs!

1509
01:54:51.050 --> 01:54:52.427
(screaming, shouting)

1510
01:54:52.427 --> 01:54:53.553
They made us, Bureau.

1511
01:54:53.553 --> 01:54:56.055
-You got a terrorist shooting hostages.
-I see it. Bank left.

1512
01:55:03.396 --> 01:55:05.106
Nail that sucker!

1513
01:55:13.197 --> 01:55:16.284
I'm on your side, you assholes!

1514
01:55:16.284 --> 01:55:19.329
Shit. Swing around again!
I'll bag this little bastard.

1515
01:55:39.098 --> 01:55:41.100
What the fuck-- Jesus!

1516
01:55:43.186 --> 01:55:45.563
Oh, John, what the fuck are you doing?

1517
01:55:45.563 --> 01:55:48.149
How the fuck did you get into this shit?

1518
01:55:50.276 --> 01:55:53.446
(screaming, shouting continues)

1519
01:55:58.743 --> 01:55:59.744
There's something wrong.

1520
01:55:59.744 --> 01:56:01.412
They're coming back down.

1521
01:56:01.412 --> 01:56:03.748
-Blow the roof.
-But Karl's up there!

1522
01:56:03.748 --> 01:56:05.166
Blow the roof!

1523
01:56:08.419 --> 01:56:11.589
I promise I will never even think

1524
01:56:11.589 --> 01:56:14.175
about going up in a tall building again.

1525
01:56:17.553 --> 01:56:19.806
Oh, God. Please don't let me die.

1526
01:56:32.610 --> 01:56:34.779
-Holy shit!
-(yelling)

1527
01:57:01.472 --> 01:57:03.766
(panting)

1528
01:57:03.766 --> 01:57:04.767
(groans)

1529
01:57:24.662 --> 01:57:27.248
(screaming)

1530
01:57:27.248 --> 01:57:28.624
(shouts in French)

1531
01:57:51.564 --> 01:57:53.608
Holy Christ!

1532
01:57:55.401 --> 01:57:57.904
We're gonna need some more FBI guys,
I guess.

1533
01:57:57.904 --> 01:57:59.781
(gasping)

1534
01:58:07.330 --> 01:58:08.539
(dings)

1535
01:58:10.708 --> 01:58:12.627
Jesus fucking Christ!

1536
01:58:24.680 --> 01:58:26.682
(clattering)

1537
01:58:38.903 --> 01:58:40.905
What the fuck is going on?

1538
01:58:43.741 --> 01:58:44.784
HOLLY: What are you gonna do,

1539
01:58:44.784 --> 01:58:46.953
sit here while the building
falls down around your ears?

1540
01:58:47.245 --> 01:58:48.871
MAN (shouting in German)

1541
01:58:55.753 --> 01:58:58.798
-Shit!
-Hey! All right!

1542
01:58:58.798 --> 01:59:00.716
(shouts in French)

1543
01:59:02.260 --> 01:59:03.970
Hang on, baby.

1544
01:59:03.970 --> 01:59:05.596
Hang on, honey.

1545
01:59:05.596 --> 01:59:07.431
Oh, God.

1546
01:59:45.344 --> 01:59:47.847
BOTH (shouting in French)

1547
01:59:52.560 --> 01:59:54.061
McCLANE: Hans!

1548
02:00:09.410 --> 02:00:10.578
Jesus.

1549
02:00:11.495 --> 02:00:12.830
Hi, honey.

1550
02:00:35.478 --> 02:00:37.021
So that's what this was all about?

1551
02:00:37.021 --> 02:00:39.023
A fucking robbery?

1552
02:00:39.023 --> 02:00:40.566
Put down the gun.

1553
02:00:42.568 --> 02:00:44.612
Why did you have to nuke
the whole building, Hans?

1554
02:00:44.612 --> 02:00:47.698
When you steal $600,
you can just disappear.

1555
02:00:47.698 --> 02:00:50.785
When you steal 600 million,
they will find you,

1556
02:00:50.785 --> 02:00:53.079
unless they think you're already dead.

1557
02:00:53.371 --> 02:00:55.414
Put down the gun.

1558
02:01:02.880 --> 02:01:04.423
(gasps)

1559
02:01:05.841 --> 02:01:07.510
HANS:<i> Nein! </i>This is mine.

1560
02:01:10.680 --> 02:01:12.807
You got me.

1561
02:01:12.807 --> 02:01:15.601
HANS: Still the cowboy, Mr. McClane.

1562
02:01:15.601 --> 02:01:17.561
Americans, all alike.

1563
02:01:17.561 --> 02:01:21.107
Well, this time, John Wayne does not walk
off into the sunset with Grace Kelly.

1564
02:01:21.399 --> 02:01:23.109
That's Gary Cooper, asshole.

1565
02:01:23.109 --> 02:01:25.027
Enough jokes.

1566
02:01:25.027 --> 02:01:27.989
You'd have made a pretty good
cowboy yourself, Hans.

1567
02:01:28.906 --> 02:01:30.157
Oh, yes.

1568
02:01:30.157 --> 02:01:32.451
What was it you said to me before?

1569
02:01:33.619 --> 02:01:36.664
Yippee-ki-yea, motherfucker.

1570
02:01:36.664 --> 02:01:37.915
McCLANE (laughing)

1571
02:01:57.476 --> 02:01:58.811
Holly!

1572
02:02:04.483 --> 02:02:05.776
Happy trails, Hans.

1573
02:02:10.823 --> 02:02:12.908
(screams)

1574
02:02:19.790 --> 02:02:21.667
(screams)

1575
02:02:50.154 --> 02:02:52.239
I hope that's not a hostage.

1576
02:03:18.140 --> 02:03:21.018
(siren wailing)

1577
02:03:21.018 --> 02:03:24.855
MAN: Give me water hook-ups for engine
companies five, three, nine, six.

1578
02:03:28.692 --> 02:03:31.278
MAN #2: Over here. It's a better angle.

1579
02:03:31.278 --> 02:03:33.614
MAN #1: Let's give 'em a hand over there.

1580
02:03:35.241 --> 02:03:37.284
Keep it going now. Keep it going.

1581
02:03:43.082 --> 02:03:45.126
Come on. Come on! We're gonna miss it.

1582
02:03:45.126 --> 02:03:47.211
-Okay, hand me my notes.
-Come on!

1583
02:03:47.211 --> 02:03:49.713
Keep that water on there.

1584
02:04:09.733 --> 02:04:11.610
What was it like in there?
How did they treat you?

1585
02:04:11.610 --> 02:04:13.070
Did they frighten you at all? Any comment?

1586
02:04:13.070 --> 02:04:15.281
It was terrible.
We don't wanna talk about it.

1587
02:04:15.281 --> 02:04:18.534
-REPORTER: How does it feel to be outside?
-(mouths words)

1588
02:04:44.310 --> 02:04:46.187
(laughing)

1589
02:04:51.775 --> 02:04:53.194
(laughing)

1590
02:04:55.321 --> 02:04:56.947
(sighs)

1591
02:04:59.950 --> 02:05:01.994
Al, this is my wife Holly.

1592
02:05:01.994 --> 02:05:03.245
Holly Gennero.

1593
02:05:04.288 --> 02:05:07.958
-Holly McClane.
-Hello, Holly.

1594
02:05:07.958 --> 02:05:09.835
You got yourself a good man.

1595
02:05:09.835 --> 02:05:11.378
You take good care of him.

1596
02:05:12.713 --> 02:05:14.131
-ROBINSON: McClane?
-MAN: Yeah, it's okay. Let him through.

1597
02:05:14.131 --> 02:05:16.342
McClane, I wanna debrief.

1598
02:05:16.342 --> 02:05:20.179
I want a debriefing.
You got some things to answer for, mister.

1599
02:05:20.179 --> 02:05:23.265
Ellis's murder, for one thing.
Property damage.

1600
02:05:23.265 --> 02:05:25.351
Interfering with police business.

1601
02:05:25.351 --> 02:05:27.853
(screaming)

1602
02:06:05.975 --> 02:06:09.061
ROBINSON: All right, I want two of you to
go inside and see if there's anybody else.

1603
02:06:09.061 --> 02:06:11.105
MAN: Yes, sir. I'll take the left.

1604
02:06:18.821 --> 02:06:20.406
-MAN: Watch it!
-Whoa.

1605
02:06:20.739 --> 02:06:22.366
This one's with me.

1606
02:06:29.164 --> 02:06:32.418
-(horn honking)
-MAN: Five, four, three, two.

1607
02:06:32.710 --> 02:06:35.170
Mr. McClane. Mr. McClane,
now that it's all over,

1608
02:06:35.170 --> 02:06:38.257
after this incredible ordeal,
what are your feelings?

1609
02:06:39.383 --> 02:06:42.136
BYSTANDERS (laughing)

1610
02:06:43.804 --> 02:06:45.222
Well, well, well.

1611
02:06:46.181 --> 02:06:48.267
-Merry Christmas, Argyle.
-Merry Christmas.

1612
02:06:52.980 --> 02:06:54.023
Did you get that?

1613
02:06:54.023 --> 02:06:57.192
Let me through. Let me through.
Thank you.

1614
02:06:57.192 --> 02:07:00.279
If this is their idea of Christmas,
I gotta be here for New Year's.

1615
02:07:05.909 --> 02:07:09.705
<i>♪ Oh, the weather outside is frightful ♪</i>

1616
02:07:09.788 --> 02:07:13.834
<i>♪ But the fire is so delightful ♪</i>

1617
02:07:13.917 --> 02:07:17.129
<i>♪ And since we've no place to go ♪</i>

1618
02:07:17.212 --> 02:07:21.258
<i>♪ Let it snow, let it snow, let it snow ♪</i>

1619
02:07:21.342 --> 02:07:25.095
<i>♪ It doesn't show signs of stopping ♪</i>

1620
02:07:25.179 --> 02:07:28.932
<i>♪ And I've brought some corn for popping ♪</i>

1621
02:07:29.016 --> 02:07:32.186
<i>♪ The lights are turned way down low ♪</i>

1622
02:07:32.269 --> 02:07:36.148
<i>♪ Let it snow, let it snow, let it snow ♪</i>

1623
02:07:36.231 --> 02:07:39.777
<i>♪ When we finally kiss good night ♪</i>

1624
02:07:39.860 --> 02:07:43.572
<i>♪ How I hate going out in the storm ♪</i>

1625
02:07:43.656 --> 02:07:47.660
<i>♪ But if you really hold me tight ♪</i>

1626
02:07:47.743 --> 02:07:51.413
<i>♪ All the way home I'll be warm ♪</i>

1627
02:07:51.497 --> 02:07:54.958
<i>♪ The fire is slowly dying ♪</i>

1628
02:07:55.042 --> 02:07:58.379
<i>♪ And, my dear we're still good-byeing ♪</i>

1629
02:07:58.462 --> 02:08:02.466
<i>♪ But as long as you love me so ♪</i>

1630
02:08:02.549 --> 02:08:09.098
<i>♪ Let it snow, let it snow, let it snow ♪♪</i>

1631
02:08:15.646 --> 02:08:18.273
<i>♪♪ (opera)</i>

1632
